column5: Well Zac was borded tonight so i said grab your rod let see is anything is hitting off the dock...wasn't long the bobbers were sinking ...it was none stop action for over 1hr with tons of blue gills and some nice size slabs ...but soon as Zoe starting buggin us on the dock the crappies disapered ...all in all we have a nice Crappie dinner for tommrow night ...
Are you saying im a white bucket fisherman ???? quote we did realease over 40 fish for you to try and catch HTH
No, no, "white bucketeers" use round buckets, you're safe.
A man a boy and a dog with a bucket of panfish. Sounds like a good day to me. I'm hoping to get my own bucket out later this week.  Congrats on a nice outing!!!
Ya, sure, rub my nose in it......(dude), looks like ya both had a good time!
Hi Fishmaster,  Can we fish overnight or early morning Sat or Sunday, we used to see you in Sunday Morning and paid you. When is the crappie and Walleye fishing season end?  Thanks in advance!

Yes you can fish here day or night ...i was thinking of trying for these Crappies at night myself ...Walleye Closes last day in Feb ...Crappie is open all year as for how long do the walleye and crappies stay in the river ...Walleye year round ...Crappies Spring Fall & Winter
